      • getPluginByTitle

        public static <T extends UnspecificPlugin> T getPluginByTitle(Class<T> clazz,
                                                              String title,
                                                              Locale language)
        The function getPluginByTitle() loads all plug-ins implementing the given UnspecificPlugin class type and returns a redirection class to handle the first plug-in implementation object that responds to getTitle(language) with the given title.

        Currently, this method is not referenced from within the Production code, but this may change in future. The function is provided to show how the old plug-in API can be replaced in future.

        Parameters:
        clazz - UnspecificPlugin class type of the plug-ins to load
        title - title the plug-in implementation object shall respond with
        language - language the title is in (may be null)
        Returns:
        the first plug-in that responds with the given title
